description: Back in the old days, people used these things to make butter. These days, of course, we have more sophisticated methods of buttercraft, like magic tables.

name: Tin Bucket

name: Withergate Barn Arch
description: An spooktacular arch that proves subtlety is the enemy of style.

name: Danger Poster
description: Danger: You are on a farm with KILLER style.

name: No Sailing Poster
description: This sign is sure to keep those pesky sailboats away.

name: Iron Feeding Trough
description: A sturdy trough that will hold a feast of animal feed for your barn animal buddies.

name: Red Oil Drum

name: Empty Planter

description: Behold, the greatest feat of Demonic engineering: Indoor plumbing!!

name: Thick Green Pipe
description: Bog water, swimming pool water, slime... these pipes are designed to handle it all.

name: Line of Pipes
description: A nice and orderly row of pipes. Just... don't ask where they go.

name: Elven Window
description: Nature is outside your window. Now, it can be ON your window, too.

name: Nel'Vari Barn Arch
description: Old oakwood, bent into an arch and festooned with deep forest vines and lillies.

name: Hanging Spool of Rope
description: A length of rope, kept nice and tidy for whenever it may be needed.

name: Rake
description: What kind of weird farming tool is this? It's like some kind of weird comb on a stick... what did the farmers of old use it for, you wonder.

name: Pirate Anchor
description: Her anchorin' days are over. Now she just makes a fine wall decoration.

name: Pirate Bed
description: The finest bed buried treasure can buy.

name: Pirate Cannon
description: A big ol' honkin' cannon... though it's only a replica and can't actually be fired. Too bad!

name: Pirate Chair
description: I didn't know chairs could be pirates. Arrrrr.

name: Pirate Chest
description: Don't get your hopes up - there's no lost treasure inside, it's just a cute decorative chest.

name: Pirate Hammock
description: An old piece of ship sail, repurposed into a primitive pirate hammock.

name: Pirate Treasure Map
description: A tattered treasure map, showing the location of a legendary pirate treasure. Too bad you were always bad at reading maps!

name: Pirate Wardrobe
description: Keep your spare peglegs organized and stored away in this barrel keg of a wardrobe.

name: Pirate Wood Post
description: Sturdy wooden posts that'll keep a ship tied to shore, so it doesn't float away in the waves!

name: Seaside Bed
description: She sleeps in seashells by the sea snore.

name: Seaside Chair
description: Sitting is great, but don't forget to stand up occasionally and stretch your fins.

name: Seaside Chest
description: Merfolk are great at restoring dingy old pirate treasure chests into cute little numbers like this one.

name: Seaside End Table
description: The only table you need while you kick back on a tropical seaside shore.

name: Seaside Lamp
description: It's hard to light a lantern under the sea (well, actually, it's sort of impossible). To adapt to life under the waves, the merfolk people use enchanted pearls that glow with light.

name: Seaside Table
description: Many a merfolk diplomatic debate (and tea party) has been had over tables like this.

name: Seaside Wardrobe
description: This fancy wardrobe is watertight up to 4,000 meters!

name: Blue Seaside Shell Rug
description: The world might be your oyster, but this clam can be your rug.

name: Blue Seaside Starfish Rug
description: Did you know that starfish can have as many as 15,000 suction cups across their body? Well, not this one, though. Because this one is a rug.

name: Pink Seaside Shell Rug
description: The world might be your oyster, but this clam can be your rug.

name: Pink Seaside Starfish Rug
description: Did you know that starfish can have as many as 15,000 suction cups across their body? Well, not this one, though. Because this one is a rug.

name: Mushroom Bed
description: Lay your head down on the velvety mushroom caps and dream your mushroomy dreams.

name: Mushroom Bookshelf
description: Filled with books and mushrooms. Mostly mushrooms, though.

name: Mushroom Carpet
description: A supple linen carpet, depicting adorable little mushrooms along its borders.

name: Mushroom Coat Rack
description: Someone hand carved little mushrooms to hang your coat on - how adorable!

name: Mushroom Table
description: Put your coffee, your mushrooms - or heck, even your mushroom coffee, on this thing.

name: Mushroom End Table
description: A little mushroom table. Mush room for everything you want to put on it, yes.

name: Red Mushroom Decoration
description: A clay mushroom created by skilled Elven clay workers - it looks shockingly lifelike!

name: Light Brown Mushroom Decoration
description: A clay mushroom created by skilled Elven clay workers - it looks shockingly lifelike!

description: Keep the spirit of spring on your farm all year long with this seasonally themed selling portal!

name: Summer Selling Portal
description: Keep the spirit of summer on your farm all year long with this seasonally themed selling portal!

name: Fall Selling Portal
description: Keep the spirit of fall on your farm all year long with this seasonally themed selling portal!

name: Winter Selling Portal
description: Keep the spirit of winter on your farm all year long with this seasonally themed selling portal!

name: Dizzite
description: Gems like this aren't usually found in Sun Haven. Dizzy must have brought it here from another land.

name: Monster Juicer
description: For turning monster crops into monster juice. Juices provide restorative properties.

name: Monster Crafting Table
description: A monstrous work bench outfitted with strange tools the likes you've never seen before.

name: Elven Crafting Table
description: An enchanted stump stocked with highly specialized Elven tools.

name: Elven Juicer
description: Turns Nel'Vari crops into juice - it works so well you'd swear it was magic! Juices provide restorative properties.

name: Woven Wood Fence
description: Elven wood that has been intricately woven together in a mesmerizingly beautiful yet sturdy fence.

name: Woven Wood Gate
description: Mere fence gates, though they're more beautiful than any door you've ever seen.

name: Wheat
description: Perfectly versatile; it can be turned into flour for people, or turned into feed for your farm animals.

name: Corn
description: A fresh ear of corn, it's not very good for eating uncooked, but it makes excellent popcorn.

name: Potato
description: Potatoes are a starchy vegetable, perfect for dishes that fortify the body.

name: Tomato
description: If tomatoes are a fruit, does that make tomato soup a type of juice? The perfect question to ruminate on as you cook your meal.

name: Demon Orb
description: A perfectly round sphere of demonic energy, what could it possibly be used for?

name: Snappy Plant
description: Snips and bites at seemingly anything that comes close to it, a favored houseplant for many in Withergate.

name: Carrot
description: Surprisingly high in sugar, carrots are a cornerstone of flavor in many different types of dishes.

name: Shimmeroot
description: Shimmering with flakes of gold, it's not hard to see where this root got its name.

name: Pepper
description: Some people argue that the spice is an acquired taste, but this fiery pepper is great for adding an edge to any dish.

name: Onion
description: The traditional ingredient of choice for a sweet, savory flavor in any dish. Just try not to cry when you cut them!

name: Greenroot
description: Most think it's a weed, but it can be ground into a spice that livens up any dish.

name: Cinnaberry
description: Crunchy and bursting with unique spice, these berries are imperative for creating the perfect dessert.

name: Lettuce
description: A very mild flavor makes this vegetable excellent for pairing up with many different ingredients.

name: Rice
description: Full of starch, you may be surprised how filling these little grains can be.

name: Eggplant
description: The skin of this peculiar plant resembles an eggshell, but it doesn't sound hollow. What does the inside taste like?

name: Kraken Kale
description: Many monsters claim this strange crop tastes great when served with noodles. Maybe you'll just take their word for it.

name: Moonplant
description: Much like its namesake, the flower of this plant reflects light, seeming to shine just like the moon.

name: Suckerstem
description: Resembling an average snack, the sickly sweet sap that drips from this crop can actually be quite overwhelming.

name: Tombmelon
description: This uncanny gourd grows naturally around tombs, making it fairly common around a place like Withergate.

name: Razorstalk
description: Though fibrous and very much leaf-like, these stalks are still sharp as razors.

name: Soul Orb
description: A wispy sphere of pure energy, though it moves like a flame it is faintly chill to the touch.

name: Grapes
description: The unmatchable sweetness of these grapes more than makes up for the effort it takes to grow them.

name: Water Fruit
description: A soft sphere of water, the easiest way to consume this melon is to pop a straw right into it and drink away!

name: Fire Fruit
description: Flaming hot, they're hard to handle and even harder to eat, but very few fruits compare to the raging flavor of this berry.

name: Rock Fruit
description: Calling this fruit 'hard as rocks' would be an understatement. Don't chip a tooth!

name: Wind Chime
description: Some Elves in Nel'Vari claim they can play this wispy sprout as a sort of musical instrument.

name: Dragon Fruit
description: Beloved by dragons and anyone else who can tolerate the spice of this fruit's fiery seeds.

name: Walk Choy
description: A crisp leaf dropped by a Walk Choy as a way of thanking you for helping it grow.

name: Shiiwalki Mushroom
description: A skinny mushroom stalk dropped by a Shiiwalki Mushroom as a way of thanking you for helping it grow.

name: Indiglow
description: Though a single lily gives off only faint glow, bundles of this flower are a popular decoration, and light source, for Nel'Varian homes.

name: Acorn
description: Bitter when raw but sweet and nutty once baked, a famous ingredient in Nel'Varian pies.

name: Cat Tail
description: Grassy stalks topped with a fuzzy brown 'tail' that no cat can resist the urge to pounce and paw at.

name: Mana Gem
description: Imbued with the mana of many different people, these beautiful gems glow with a soothing aura.

name: Guava Berry
description: Every part of this fruit is edible, from the seeds to the rind!

name: Pumpkin
description: Technically a fruit. A big, hard orange fruit.

name: Hops
description: Tiny little flower buds that are crucial to the brewing process.

name: Soda Pop Crop
description: The buds of this crop fizz with air, making it the most important ingredient in the four region's hottest new drink: soda!

name: Fizzy Fruit
description: This curious plant naturally creates fizzy air when brewed, fizzing up any drink they're used in.

name: Turnip
description: Turn up with turnip, if you know what's good for you.

name: Heat Fruit
description: The fruit literal glows with heat. Watch your fingers!

name: Marshmallow Bean
description: Looks a bit like a bean, but tastes like a marshmallow. Name checks out.

name: Butternut
description: Better a squash than a smoosh.

name: Barley
description: The grain of this crop is high in fiber, but more importantly, it's useful in brewing!

name: Yam
description: Jam out with your yam out.

name: Tea Leaves
description: How can anyone ever be sick of tea? That’s like being sick of breathing!

name: Ghost Pepper
description: If you're brave enough to try one of these ultra hot peppers just remember to drink milk and not water!

name: Kale
description: It might not taste like much, but kale is super healthy.

name: Stormelon
description: A species of melon created by Elemental enchanters that contains the elemental force of storm.

name: Lemon
description: Sour fruit, it can be tempered with sugar.

name: Armoranth
description: This poofy flower might look soft, but its petals are as hard as iron.

name: Chocoberry
description: A standard semi-sweet chocolate on their own, but using them in recipes brings out their true sweetness.

name: Clover
description: Do you think it's a lucky one?

name: Pineapple
description: Good for living in under the sea.

name: Melon
description: Soft, ripe and perfect for a hot summer day.

name: Heart Berry
description: A berry whose juice is often served as a drink during romantic meals.

name: Coffee Bean
description: This bean turns into a magical drink when brewed in a keg.

name: Garlic
description: Pungent as garlic may be, it's a great addition to many dishes.

name: Mango
description: It's like an apple's tropical island cousin.

name: Durian
description: This fruit stinks! Literally!

name: Balloon Fruit
description: This wild fruit actually floats into the sky as a way of distributing its seeds.

name: Blue Moon Fruit
description: This fruit only grows once in a blue moon, but it is worth it for a taste of the night.

name: Hexagon Berry
description: Hexagons are nature's ultimate shape. Therefore, these are nature's ultimate berry.

name: Star Fruit
description: Sure to be the star of whatever dish you prepare it in.

name: Snow Ball Crop
description: These snowballs are not for throwing!

name: Blizzard Berry
description: These berries grow best when encased under the snow of fresh blizzards.

name: Pythagorean Berry
description: Forget trying to pronounce the name. Just eat the fruit!

name: Cranberry
description: Cranberries are highly valued for the sweet sauce they're cooked into for holiday feasts.

name: Kiwi Berry
description: A fruit native to a specific island within the Southern Islands chain.

name: Green Beans
description: They're beans and they are most certainly green.

name: Peas
description: Pass the peas, please.

name: Watermelon
description: Best enjoyed by the slice.

name: Cotton
description: It may be second to wool, but cotton is never forgotten.

name: Honeysuckle
description: Flowering vines that are found native in the tundras of the Northern Region.

name: Candy Cane
description: The most popular winter candy.

name: Snow Pea
description: There's no peas like snow peas.

name: Sun Orb
description: A burning orb of energy, its warmth alone is revitalizing.

name: Dead Crop
description: Withered and crumbling, it's as if these vines didn't get enough energy...

name: Honey Flower
description: Despite their name, they don't taste like honey - they just taste like  flowers. For a real honey taste, well, thats what you need the bees for.

name: Lavender
description: Legends say that this vibrant purple flower originally grew deep in Elven forests before adapting to the less magical soils of Sun Haven.

name: Hibiscus
description: People in the Southern Isles often wear these flowers in their hair for special occassions, a fashion choice that hasn't quite spread to the rest of the lands yet.

name: Lily
description: These beautiful flowers were brought to these lands from a far away continent. They grow very well here despite not being a native species.

name: Orchid
description: In some areas of the land an orchid represents strength and loyalty, in others it is an omen of bad luck.

name: Sunflower
description: The official flower of Sun Haven, often used to represent one's appreciation of Elios the Sun Dragon. So, sun flowers in Sun Haven for the Sun Dragon.

name: Red Rose
description: Brilliant red roses are a symbol of royalty and everlasting love, a staple in romantic bouquets.

name: Blue Rose
description: Graceful blue roses are a symbol of peace and elegance, in the Eastern Region these roses replace the red variety in wedding ceremonies.

name: Tulip
description: Tulips grow by the thousands in waving fields across the warmer parts of the Northern Region.

name: Lotus
description: The flowers of the lotus plant are known for representing renewal, blooming each day with a refreshed beauty.
